This paper focuses on the practice of patch construction in software development, which is a core topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of bug detection tools and automatic patch generation, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of tool support on patch construction, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
